    <br>
    <!-- Paragraphs about pickleball as a habit -->
    <p>Pickleball is one of those rare sports that’s easy to pick up but hard to stop playing.
        It blends elements of tennis, badminton, and ping‑pong into a fast, social game that rewards
        quick thinking more than raw power. Whether you’re rallying at the kitchen line or laughing
        through a missed volley, pickleball manages to be competitive, welcoming, and surprisingly
        addictive—all at the same time.</p>
    <br>
